[The total number of cases in this multistate outbreak of listeriosis related to ricotta salata cheese has risen from 15 to 20 and the number of deaths from 3 to 4 since the last ProMED-mail post [Listeriosis - USA (03): fatal, cheese, recall, update 20120923.1305794] on this outbreak. 9 of the illnesses were related to a pregnancy; 3 of these illnesses were diagnosed in newborns. One fetal loss has also been reported. DNA "fingerprints", -- that is, genotyping, of listeria have been used to identify cases of illness that are linked to this outbreak.

